MODEL: claude-opus-4-8
CWD: ~/systems

Read ~/fable-window/RULES.md and obey it.
Build a NEW additive cron: creative fatigue sentinel. New directory ~/systems/fatigue-sentinel/ (creating new files there is allowed; do not modify any existing script). Study ~/systems/bq-clickup-perf/bq_to_clickup_perf.py for the working bq CLI + SA auth pattern and ~/systems/watchdog/box-watchdog.sh for the ntfy pattern (topic tomas-tab-958e4431).
Logic (single BQ query against ejam-dwh.production.creative_dashboard, SA ~/.config/gcloud/ejam-dwh-sa.json, grain ad_id x day):
- Active set: ads with spend in the last 2 days above a floor (default $50/day, configurable at top of script).
- For each: hook rate = view_3s_count/impressions, hold = video_p100_count/video_play_count (video only), roas = revenue/spend, last-48h value vs trailing 7-day mean (exclude the 48h from the baseline).
- Alert condition: a WINNER decaying - baseline roas above breakeven AND (hook rate down more than 20% relative OR roas down more than 30% relative) with minimum impression volume to avoid noise (default 10k impressions in the 48h window).
- Output: one ntfy push (Priority high) listing top 5 decaying ads by spend: creative code (REGEXP_EXTRACT(ad_name, r"(SH-\d+(?:-\d+)+)") fallback ad_id), spend, roas now vs baseline, hook now vs baseline. No alert = no push, but every Monday send a Priority min "sentinel alive, N ads watched" heartbeat.
Deliver: fatigue_sentinel.py + run_sentinel.sh + a systemd unit pair (service + timer, daily 08:30) written to ~/systems/fatigue-sentinel/ but NOT installed/enabled - staging only, Tomas enables via systemd/install.sh after review. VERIFY: actually run run_sentinel.sh once in test mode (--dry-run flag that prints the would-be push instead of sending, except send ONE real Priority min test push tagged [TEST] so delivery is proven). Save the dry-run output to ~/fable-window/artifacts/fatigue-sentinel.dryrun.md. Update the ledger per RULES.
